[{"question":"How many times have you been properly in love before you met Karen?","answer":"Never.","docId":"120120pmt","qSentId":2,"aSentId":3},{"question":"Never?","answer":"No.","docId":"120120pmt","qSentId":4,"aSentId":5},{"question":"Let\u0027s just make it chummy, aren\u0027t we?","answer":"Yes.","docId":"120120pmt","qSentId":40,"aSentId":41},{"question":"Right?","answer":"It seems like a crazy period as this election really hits off.","docId":"120120pmt","qSentId":47,"aSentId":48},{"question":"How do you feel?","answer":"You know, I\u0027m a slow and steady kind of guy.","docId":"120120pmt","qSentId":49,"aSentId":50},{"question":"Really?","answer":"No.","docId":"120120pmt","qSentId":77,"aSentId":78},{"question":"Has Mitt Romney called you and congratulated you about winning Iowa?","answer":"As a matter of fact he did, you know, shortly -- shortly afterwards, yesterday afternoon.","docId":"120120pmt","qSentId":89,"aSentId":90},{"question":"So this gets interesting, doesn\u0027t it?","answer":"It\u0027s as -- as I said in New Hampshire, and -- and also in Iowa, game on.","docId":"120120pmt","qSentId":105,"aSentId":106},{"question":"-- the race?","answer":"-- I think that\u0027s a pretty good analysis of the race.","docId":"120120pmt","qSentId":133,"aSentId":134},{"question":"Yes?","answer":"-- that you were the guy with the big ideas.","docId":"120120pmt","qSentId":141,"aSentId":142},{"question":"Why has such an incredibly aggressive, fast-moving, seemingly formidable movement dissipated to the extent that it has?","answer":"It is a little bit confounding that here\u0027s a group that was this -- the -- the key -- absolutely the key for the Republicans to win in 2008.","docId":"120120pmt","qSentId":164,"aSentId":165},{"question":"Do you think your trump card is that you have flip- flopped the least and that you are -- you are -- whether people agree with you or not, you\u0027ve been the most true to your principles?","answer":"I certainly make that case, that they\u0027re borne out of real convictions and I\u0027ve tried to reflect those convictions in every aspect of my life.","docId":"120120pmt","qSentId":172,"aSentId":173},{"question":"-- the war generation, weren\u0027t they?","answer":"Yes, I mean it inspires you to realize the sacrifice that people make and make today.","docId":"120120pmt","qSentId":242,"aSentId":243},{"question":"If you\u0027d been president after 9/11, would you have gone to war in Iraq, knowing everything you know now?","answer":"It would have been a very hard decision.","docId":"120120pmt","qSentId":251,"aSentId":252},{"question":"So what\u0027s the answer?","answer":"Based on the information I had at the time, I think we made the right decision.","docId":"120120pmt","qSentId":261,"aSentId":262},{"question":"But what about everything you know now?","answer":"Yes, it\u0027s hard to -- it\u0027s hard to go back and Monday morning quarterbacking.","docId":"120120pmt","qSentId":263,"aSentId":264},{"question":"We left on a cliffhanger there, where you were mulling over the nuances of, with all the evidence we now have, would you have gone to war in Iraq?","answer":".","docId":"120120pmt","qSentId":276,"aSentId":277},{"question":"Do you think the mission was finished?","answer":"The mission was partially finished.","docId":"120120pmt","qSentId":290,"aSentId":291},{"question":"If you become president in November, would you put American troops back into Iraq?","answer":"No.","docId":"120120pmt","qSentId":292,"aSentId":293},{"question":"So, the genie is out of the bottle?","answer":"The genie is out of the bottle and you have to deal with the situation as it is.","docId":"120120pmt","qSentId":298,"aSentId":299},{"question":"Would you be prepared to put boots on the ground in Iran?","answer":"No.","docId":"120120pmt","qSentId":300,"aSentId":301},{"question":"How you would you do it?","answer":"In fact, I\u0027ve laid out a pretty clear road map, if you will, as to the things that I think we need to do, and I have stopped short of saying we need to put boots on the ground.","docId":"120120pmt","qSentId":302,"aSentId":303},{"question":"You wouldn\u0027t hesitate to bomb Iran if you had to?","answer":"Absolutely not hesitate to do --","docId":"120120pmt","qSentId":306,"aSentId":307},{"question":"What would it take to trigger that, do you think?","answer":"ANTORUM: That I felt that they were on the precipice of, you know, actually being in a position to produce that nuclear weapon.","docId":"120120pmt","qSentId":308,"aSentId":309},{"question":"And just being on the cusp of being able to produce it, you think would be enough to trigger an attack?","answer":"It would because once that weapon is weaponized and completed and exploded, then we have a situation where the world has changed.","docId":"120120pmt","qSentId":311,"aSentId":312},{"question":"Gadhafi taken out with allied help?","answer":"You know, again, my feeling on that is that we, number one, acted indecisively, we acted unwisely, we acted at the behest of international bodies without a national security interest in our -- and I would not engaged.","docId":"120120pmt","qSentId":325,"aSentId":326},{"question":"Didn\u0027t it?","answer":"Well, let\u0027s find -- well, certainly Gadhafi is gone.","docId":"120120pmt","qSentId":329,"aSentId":330},{"question":"So, you -- by the process of elimination, you would have kept Gadhafi in power?","answer":"I would only act using the American military if there is a national security interest to our country was threatened.","docId":"120120pmt","qSentId":345,"aSentId":346},{"question":"So would be happy to say China, as its military power increases, to start doing some of the dirty work, perhaps, at being the global police force?","answer":"I\u0027m not sure the dirty work wouldn\u0027t be rather dirty as opposed to what we do, which is not dirty work, which is stand up and -- for human rights and stand up for liberty and for the opportunity of people to have political and economic freedom.","docId":"120120pmt","qSentId":365,"aSentId":366},{"question":"-- personally?","answer":"I\u0027ve -- I served with him for two years.","docId":"120120pmt","qSentId":369,"aSentId":370},{"question":"Why?","answer":"-- from a professional point of view.","docId":"120120pmt","qSentId":375,"aSentId":376},{"question":"What\u0027s your main criticism of him as president?","answer":"Well, I think he has a fundamental different view of what -- what makes America a great country.","docId":"120120pmt","qSentId":378,"aSentId":379},{"question":"What do you think his view is?","answer":"His view is that the stronger the government is and the more things that I can do for its people, the better this country is going to be.","docId":"120120pmt","qSentId":380,"aSentId":381},{"question":"And what\u0027s your view?","answer":"My view is the less the government can do and the more freedom and opportunity you give people, that trusting people and free people and free enterprise -- that America has built the greatest country in the history of the world.","docId":"120120pmt","qSentId":382,"aSentId":383},{"question":"Given your stance on gay marriage, for example, could you see any circumstances where you might change that in a way that you hardened your position on an issue like abortion, could you see yourself potentially softening your position on gay marriage?","answer":"No, you know, marriage is an institution that existed before governments existed.","docId":"120120pmt","qSentId":397,"aSentId":398},{"question":"So when you say you respect their rights, isn\u0027t their legal right in New York now to get married?","answer":"Well, it\u0027s a law.","docId":"120120pmt","qSentId":405,"aSentId":406},{"question":"Would you change the law?","answer":"I would change the law to make a uniform definition of marriage in this country, because I think -- like the uniform definition for life --","docId":"120120pmt","qSentId":412,"aSentId":413},{"question":"You would make it illegal to get married?","answer":"Well, again, I would reinstitute the traditional marriage as the best --","docId":"120120pmt","qSentId":415,"aSentId":416},{"question":"Are you going to try to make it illegal for gay people to get married?","answer":"All I would say is that marriage has been voted on 32 times in this country in 32 states, from Maine to California and 32 times the people of this country have said that marriage is between a man and a woman and the public should have a say about this.","docId":"120120pmt","qSentId":424,"aSentId":425},{"question":"Why was that?","answer":"Life.","docId":"120120pmt","qSentId":427,"aSentId":428},{"question":"And was pregnant and was begging you to let her have an abortion, would you really be able to look her in the eye and say, no, as her father?","answer":"I would do what every father must do, is to try to counsel your daughter to do the right thing.","docId":"120120pmt","qSentId":437,"aSentId":438},{"question":"And they are looking at their daughter ,saying, how can I deal with this, because if I make her have this baby, isn\u0027t it going to just ruin her life?","answer":"Well, you can make the argument that if she doesn\u0027t have this baby, if she kills her child, that that, too, could ruin her life.","docId":"120120pmt","qSentId":442,"aSentId":443},{"question":"How do you equate that with supporting the death penalty, given there are so many people who actually are completely innocent?","answer":"Yes.","docId":"120120pmt","qSentId":456,"aSentId":457},{"question":"But we can\u0027t be, can we?","answer":"Well, you can --","docId":"120120pmt","qSentId":460,"aSentId":461},{"question":"How have you managed to do this, and stay so united, so close?","answer":"I think a lot of it is just a real focus on faith and family.","docId":"120120pmt","qSentId":485,"aSentId":486},{"question":"How did you two meet?","answer":"At the law firm.","docId":"120120pmt","qSentId":519,"aSentId":520},{"question":"What was it you saw in Rick?","answer":"He was so funny the night we met.","docId":"120120pmt","qSentId":532,"aSentId":533},{"question":"It couldn\u0027t have been the sweater?","answer":"I didn\u0027t have --","docId":"120120pmt","qSentId":535,"aSentId":536},{"question":"And, Karen, what do you think is the biggest misconception about your husband?","answer":"That he\u0027s not nice.","docId":"120120pmt","qSentId":544,"aSentId":545},{"question":"-- become something different?","answer":"Absolutely.","docId":"120120pmt","qSentId":569,"aSentId":570},{"question":"But you think people should lay off him on this one?","answer":"I think, yes, that\u0027s my personal belief.","docId":"120120pmt","qSentId":578,"aSentId":579},{"question":"What was he singing?","answer":"And he said -- he said, I\u0027m not going away.","docId":"120120pmt","qSentId":608,"aSentId":609},{"question":"What were you singing, do you remember?","answer":"Well, yes, I was.","docId":"120120pmt","qSentId":613,"aSentId":614},{"question":"Really?","answer":"(Inaudible).","docId":"120120pmt","qSentId":616,"aSentId":617},{"question":"This is going to ruin everything?","answer":"A little bit.","docId":"120120pmt","qSentId":635,"aSentId":636},{"question":"Has it been a positive thing?","answer":"Yes.","docId":"120120pmt","qSentId":642,"aSentId":643},{"question":"How do you feel when the old man gets attacked?","answer":"We try not to read the news.","docId":"120120pmt","qSentId":645,"aSentId":646},{"question":"The barroom brawls, you know, if you hear someone dissing Santorum?","answer":"Yes, just ignore it.","docId":"120120pmt","qSentId":647,"aSentId":648},{"question":"Oh, you ignore it?","answer":"Yes.","docId":"120120pmt","qSentId":650,"aSentId":651},{"question":"Sarah, how do you feel?","answer":"Well, it\u0027s been really busy, but it\u0027s been quite an experience.","docId":"120120pmt","qSentId":652,"aSentId":653},{"question":"Really?","answer":"So cute, our two younger boys who are not here, they said, \"Dad, you can\u0027t run for president because you won\u0027t be able to coach Little League baseball.\"","docId":"120120pmt","qSentId":658,"aSentId":659},{"question":"In a simple, short way, why would your husband make a good president?","answer":"For so many reasons.","docId":"120120pmt","qSentId":699,"aSentId":700}]